Dia. 03 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's attachment at 1 is an excellent maek. White's liberties are reduced to two.
\par
\par White can't resist against this move. If White plays hane at 2, Black captures with 3 and 5. If White plays at A instead of 2, Black plays dansu at 4.
\par
\par
\par }
